sbol:Collection.dcterms:title: iGEM Parts Registry
sbol:Collection.dcterms:description: The iGEM Registry is a growing collection of genetic parts that can be mixed and matched to build synthetic biology devices and systems. As part of the synthetic biology community's efforts to make biology easier to engineer, it provides a source of genetic parts to iGEM teams and academic labs.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_B0012
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Transcription terminator for the E.coli RNA polymerase.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Reshma Shetty
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: Derived from the TE terminator of T7 bacteriophage between Genes 1.3 and 1.4 <genbank>V01146</genbank>.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes:
Suggested by Sri Kosuri and Drew Endy as a high efficiency terminator. The 5' end cutoff was placed immediately after the TAA stop codon and the 3' end cutoff was placed just prior to the RBS of Gene 1.4 (before AAGGAG).

Use anywhere transcription should be stopped when the gene of interest is upstream of this terminator.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_B0034
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Vinay S Mahajan, Voichita D. Marinescu, Brian Chow, Alexander D Wissner-Gross and Peter Carr IAP, 2003.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes:
Varies from -6 to +1 region from original sequence to accomodate BioBricks suffix.

No secondary structures are formed in the given RBS region. Users should check for secondary structures induced in the RBS by upstream and downstream elements in the +50 to -50 region, as such structures will greatly affect the strength of the RBS. Contact info for this part: Brian Chow

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K302033
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Encodes a stable non-specific ribonuclease in ''Bacillus Subtilis''. It is used in conjungtion with ''mazE'' in ''Bacillus Subtilis'' to provide a toxin-antitoxin in various stressful conditions. When transcribtion of both genes is turned off (as both are under contol of same promoter) ''mazE'' will be degraded faster than ''mazF''. There is then no inhibiton of ''mazF'', killing the cell.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Philip Hall
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: Sequence isolated based upon the work of Pellegrini, O., Mathy, N., Gogos, A., Shapiro, L., and Condon, C. (2005) The ''Bacillus subtilis'' ydcDE operon encodes an endoribonuclease of the MazF/PemK family and its inhibitor. ''Mol Microbiol'' 56: 1139???1148.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K899001
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Elongates a trisaccharide with the fructose unit of a sucrose substrate into an inulin polymer. Works together with part BBa_K899000 (SST).
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Andreas Kj??r
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: 7 BP from start codon we embedded an shine dalgarno sequence.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K899009
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: Doubble ribosomal binding site (FFT) (shine-dalgarno and kozak sequence)
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This is the ribosomal binding site(s) we used in front of our fructan:fructan fructosyltransferase (FFT. It consists of the kozak sequence originally from the gene when we extracted it from the jerusalem artichoke (Helianthus Tuberosus), and the shine dalgarno sequence aggaggt.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Andreas Kj??r
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: jerusalem artichoke (Helianthus Tuberosus) and modified with bacterial shine-dalgarno sequence
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: the shine dalgarno is placed 6 bp from the startcodon (optimal distance) and kozak is 4 of theese bp right before start codon.
